Danielle Alexandra Grunwald and Matthew Savage Aibel were married Feb. 3 at the Bowery Hotel in New York. Christopher Michael Quinlan, a friend of the couple who was ordained by the American Marriage Ministries for the occasion, officiated.
The bride, 32, is an associate in the real estate group of the New York law firm Stroock & Stroock & Lavan. She graduated from Williams College and received a law degree, cum laude, from Cornell.
She is the daughter of Linda J. Grunwald and Dr. Andrew M. Grunwald of Beechhurst, N.Y. The bride’s father is an invasive cardiologist in Manhasset, N.Y., affiliated with NYU Langone Health.
The groom, also 32, is a litigation associate at the New York law firm Epstein Becker & Green. He graduated from Washington University in St. Louis and received a law degree from Fordham.
He is the son of Beverly Savage and James H. Aibel of Hoboken, N.J. The groom’s mother is the executive director for Hudson County Court Appointed Special Advocates, a nonprofit organization that finds permanent homes for children in foster care. His father is a lawyer and managing director in the corporate programming office at the Bank of New York Mellon.
The couple met in December 2014 after having matched on multiple dating apps.
